cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with linear detectors such as ZF and MMSE which are commonly used in information theory for communication systems. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of low complexity detection techniques in large/massive MIMO systems which are commonly used in wireless communication networks. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the use of iterative methods for obtaining low complexity approximate inverses which can be applied to various types of detectors used in network systems. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes the use of an approximate inverse for non-linear detectors such as sphere decoders which can be seen as a machine learning problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of low complexity detection techniques in large/massive MIMO systems which are commonly used in multimedia communication applications.
